# Service-to-service auth: gateway -> ai-assistant. Template for .env.ai-proxy
# (`make up` copies this file if .env.ai-proxy is missing).
#
# The gateway attaches this as X-Internal-Auth on /ai proxy calls; ai-assistant
# refuses /intake-instructions without it. Defense in depth behind the compose
# topology (ai-assistant is not host-published).
#
# This secret lives in its OWN env file — never in the shared .env — because
# compose hands .env to every service, and any holder of the secret could
# bypass the gateway session check on the paid LLM path. Only gateway and
# ai-assistant load this file (guarded by tests/test_compose_topology.py).
#
# FAIL-CLOSED: shipped empty on purpose — a fresh copied config refuses every
# AI call (503) until a real secret is set (same class as the Bedrock bearer
# key; placeholder values like "changeme" are also treated as absent).
# Generate with:
#   openssl rand -hex 32
AI_PROXY_SHARED_SECRET=
